:"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#053","content":"README updated"},"20":{"id":"/docs/changelog-18","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#053","content":"`@jgmc/react`"},"21":{"id":"/docs/changelog-19","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#053","content":"Add key to gradient elements for react warning"},"22":{"id":"/docs/changelog-20","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#053","content":"Remove `react` as dependency, should be just peer dep"},"23":{"id":"/docs/changelog-21","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#053","content":"Export all types too"},"24":{"id":"/docs/changelog-22","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"**NEW PACKAGE!** `@jgmc/react`! Contains memoized react components for each chart type."},"25":{"id":"/docs/changelog-23","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`<BarChart />`"},"26":{"id":"/docs/changelog-24","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`<BarChartStacked />`"},"27":{"id":"/docs/changelog-25","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`<DonutChart />`"},"28":{"id":"/docs/changelog-26","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`<PieChart />`"},"29":{"id":"/docs/changelog-27","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`<LineChart />`"},"30":{"id":"/docs/changelog-28","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`@jgmc/vanilla`"},"31":{"id":"/docs/changelog-29","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"`barchart` & `barchartstacked`"},"32":{"id":"/docs/changelog-30","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"Fix: add image label width/height to created image labels"},"33":{"id":"/docs/changelog-31","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#052","content":"Fix: improper sizing when given datapoints that exceeded given width/height"},"34":{"id":"/docs/changelog-32","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#051","content":"This release is mainly just a version bump to update `README` links to the updated docs site!"},"35":{"id":"/docs/changelog-33","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Major"},"36":{"id":"/docs/changelog-34","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Update!"},"37":{"id":"/docs/changelog-35","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This is the biggest update yet by far. The entire library has been migrated to a monorepo structure with scoped packages, allowing for framework specific exports, additional optimizations, and more! Framework specific exports is also the next big feature I'm working on."},"38":{"id":"/docs/changelog-36","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"As such, the name of the package has changed, gone is `toomanycharts` and in is `@jgmc/...`!"},"39":{"id":"/docs/changelog-37","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Previously all functionality lived under `toomanycharts`, but now the math & framework agnostic code lives in `@jgmc/core`. Additionally I had one single dependency in-use for creating charts `linkedom` which is a fantastic library, but as part of this move I've removed it & am now just using strings!"},"40":{"id":"/docs/changelog-38","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"This has allowed for a `3x` speed increase, a smaller bundle size, and means aside from the `@jgmc/core` package there are now zero dependencies! Additionally strings are incredibly flexible, so right out of the box `@jgmc/vanilla` is completely SSR compatible, and can technically be used anywhere you can use a string!"},"41":{"id":"/docs/changelog-39","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"That being said framework specific exports are still on the way, so that framework strengths can be properly utilized, but in the meantime you can use `@jgmc/vanilla` in any framework, and it's already SSR compatible!"},"42":{"id":"/docs/changelog-40","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"Not only that but aside from a few exceptions, everything should work pretty much the same in terms of usage, aside from the output."},"43":{"id":"/docs/changelog-41","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"installation moved!"},"44":{"id":"/docs/changelog-42","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`toomanycharts` is now `@jgmc/vanilla`"},"45":{"id":"/docs/changelog-43","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"`@jgmc/core` for math & framework agnostic code"},"46":{"id":"/docs/changelog-44","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"removed `linkedom` dependency, now just using strings for charts"},"47":{"id":"/docs/changelog-45","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#v050","content":"all charts under `@jgmc/vanilla` return strings"},"48":{"id":"/docs/changelog-46","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"Removed `classes` option from all charts"},"49":{"id":"/docs/changelog-47","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"replacing with sensible default classes applied to chart elements"},"50":{"id":"/docs/changelog-48","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#023","content":"See Charts Classes for more info"},"51":{"id":"/docs/changelog-49","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After a long break I came back and finished up the initial implementation of the `asciiBarchart` I'd been working on. While I plan to continue with ASCII chart types I felt there was still plenty more worthwhile things to add in to SVG charts. The big one being two very common chart types - pie & donut charts! Those have both been added."},"52":{"id":"/docs/changelog-50","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Next up I will be doing some cleanup / refinement of the codebase. Standardizing some things across chart types, doing some type naming adjustments, etc... You can check the `TODO.md` in the repo for specifics."},"53":{"id":"/docs/changelog-51","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"After cleanup & refinement I'll be doing work on getting framework specific exports working."},"54":{"id":"/docs/changelog-52","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`piechart`"},"55":{"id":"/docs/changelog-53","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`donutchart`"},"56":{"id":"/docs/changelog-54","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"Experimental features are features that are in the early stages of development, and may be subject to change or removal without a major version bump."},"57":{"id":"/docs/changelog-55","page_id":"/docs/changelog","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/changelog#022","content":"`asciiBarchart`"},"58":{"