s, which goes something like:"},"426":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-33","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"Page loads"},"427":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-34","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"Chart created, added to page"},"428":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-35","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"At this point it looks normal with all bars full-width"},"429":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-36","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"`100ms` after, `scaleX` set to `0` so now the bars are suddenly gone, causing a flicker"},"430":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-37","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"The fix here is simple, and coming soon. I will add a `barStyle` option which will allow you to set inline styles for each bar, which'll get tacked onto them - avoiding the flicker."},"431":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-38","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#breakdown","content":"All that being said, the `transform-origin` is only relevant when you're moving the bars in some way, something like `opacity` or `fill` wouldn't require that at all."},"432":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples-39","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchart-examples#transformor